I would like to talk about, for example, the A. Šternfeld conference at the astronomical observatory in Warsaw on 6 December 1933, during which he presented ideas drawn from his " Introduction to Astronautism " book.
The developments of this young engineer (born in 1905) left the cold auditors and years later Šternfeld remembered that only Dr. Jan Gadomski was interested in his work.
